Ok I was able to find out a bit more on the issue:
- I have been able to reproduce this issue in node.js spawned from electron (before it was a forked process)
- since I am able to reproduce with spawn(), I tried newer node.js versions and was **not able to reproduce** with node.js >= 5.4
- I believe the crash is caused by our use of **node-weak** (https://github.com/TooTallNate/node-weak) which uses native code to implement weak ref counting of objects
